    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Job",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 27,
        "summary": "Job asserts his righteousness\u2014When the wicked are buried in death, terrors will take hold of them.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Moreover Job continued his parable, and said,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As God liveth, who hath taken away my judgment; and the Almighty, who hath vexed my soul;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "All the while my breath is in me, and the spirit of God is in my nostrils;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "My lips shall not speak wickedness, nor my tongue utter deceit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 5:4 (4\u201312).",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Deceit; Honesty.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "God forbid that I should justify you: till I die I will not remove mine integrity from me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Perseverance.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 24:15 (15\u201316); D&C 54:10. TG\u00a0Integrity; Sincere; Steadfastness.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "My righteousness I hold fast, and will not let it go: my heart shall not reproach me so long as I live.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 29:5.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 700
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Let mine enemy be as the wicked, and he that riseth up against me as the unrighteous.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For what is the hope of the hypocrite, though he hath gained, when God taketh away his soul?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 34:33 (33\u201335).",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 16:26.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 11
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Will God hear his cry when trouble cometh upon him?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 1:28.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 11:24 (21\u201325); 21:14 (14\u201315). TG\u00a0God, Access to.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Will he delight himself in the Almighty? will he always call upon God?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 11:23.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I will teach you by the hand of God: that which is with the Almighty will I not conceal.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, all ye yourselves have seen it; why then are ye thus altogether vain?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "This is the portion of a wicked man with God, and the heritage of oppressors, which they shall receive of the Almighty.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Injustice; Oppression.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "If his children be multiplied, it is for the sword: and his offspring shall not be satisfied with bread.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 28:41; 2\u00a0Ne. 23:16 (15\u201316).",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Those that remain of him shall be buried in death: and his widows shall not weep.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Though he heap up silver as the dust, and prepare raiment as the clay;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 13:25.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He may prepare it, but the just shall put it on, and the innocent shall divide the silver.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He buildeth his house as a moth, and as a booth that the keeper maketh.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The rich man shall lie down, but he shall not be gathered: he openeth his eyes, and he is not.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Terrors take hold on him as waters, a tempest stealeth him away in the night.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The east wind carrieth him away, and he departeth: and as a storm hurleth him out of his place.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For God shall cast upon him, and not spare: he would fain flee out of his hand.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Men shall clap their hands at him, and shall hiss him out of his place.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 2:15.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}